rComments: He's an amazing prof!He's really helpful and tries his best to explain. As long as you show up to class, you're good (ps. attendance is marked). HIs quizes, tests, and final, are fairly easy and you also have to do a biweekly journal entry (fairly simple). I recommend him since I went in knowing ZERO Italian and now I can speak it on a basic level!

He was an awesome professor and often tried to make classes fun. Obviously with his accent he was a little hard to understand but he explained concepts as well as he could. It is incredibly important to show up and attendance is taken. He marks fairly on tests, quizzes and journals.
Very easy going fun professor who knows his work well and with a  refreshing passion!
good prof! very friendly and shows effort in his teaching. he wants his students to do well!

Amazing Professor! Prior to being taught by him, I had lost faith in the profs that taught italian at UOttawa... He makes italian grammar seem easier than it really is and is extremely helpful with his students. Good use of PPT and Blackboard Learn too.
Great Professor! Always available to help students with whatever they may need. Is passionate about whatever subject being discussed and his English is great (targeted to first comment)

Professore Gastaldi is a kind person who really cares about his students. His marking can seem harsh at first, but he makes quizzes progressively easier to ensure that students improve. He has excellent knowledge of technology and uses ppt, videos, and other media during lectures. You will learn a lot in his class and laugh too!

I find the previous comment rather harsh and largely untrue. Professor Gastaldi may come off as being a little intimidating at first, but you soon see that he really cares about his students and their education. He puts a lot of effort into his lessons, and explains concepts well. His English is perfectly understandable, and he is a fair marker.
